name: $resourceType
desc: Returns the FHIR type name for this instance

name: $value
desc: Returns: The value of the measured amount. The value includes an implicit precision in the presentation of the value.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The value of the measured amount. The value includes an implicit precision in the presentation of the value.

name: $comparator
desc: Returns: How the value should be understood and represented - whether the actual value is greater or less than the stated value due to measurement issues; e.g. if the comparator is "<" , then the real value is < stated value.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: How the value should be understood and represented - whether the actual value is greater or less than the stated value due to measurement issues; e.g. if the comparator is "<" , then the real value is < stated value.

name: $unit
desc: Returns: A human-readable form of the unit.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A human-readable form of the unit.

name: $system
desc: Returns: The identification of the system that provides the coded form of the unit.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: The identification of the system that provides the coded form of the unit.

name: $code
desc: Returns: A computer processable form of the unit in some unit representation system.

pvardefs.name: pValue
pvardefs.desc: A computer processable form of the unit in some unit representation system.
